Backbone Model
===============

A model is the cornerstone piece in backbone where all data is saved.
Models can have many attributes and custom methods declared for them. 
They can know how to read and write to the server via Backbone's `sync` method.

	var Slide = Backbone.Model.extend({
		defaults : {},
		initialize : function (options) {
			this.parent(options);
		}
	});

